issue.body:
I have a client which skips certificate validation, but seems like it does not work in Java 8.

Sample client:

``` scala
Http
.client  
.withSessionQualifier.noFailFast
.withTlsWithoutValidation                          
.newService(s"$hostname:8888")
```

It throws this error:
`com.twitter.finagle.SslHandshakeException: General SSLEngine problem at remote address: $hostName/$hostName:8888`

However, I have a solution as following:

``` scala
  Http.client
       .withSessionQualifier.noFailFast
       .withTransport.tls(sslContext)
       .newService(s"$hostname:8888")

  private[this] class IgnorantTrustManager extends X509ExtendedTrustManager {
    def getAcceptedIssuers(): Array[X509Certificate] = new Array[X509Certificate](0)
    def checkClientTrusted(certs: Array[X509Certificate], authType: String): Unit = { }
    def checkServerTrusted(certs: Array[X509Certificate], authType: String): Unit = { }
    def checkClientTrusted(certs: Array[X509Certificate], authType: String, socket: Socket): Unit = { }
    def checkServerTrusted(certs: Array[X509Certificate], authType: String, socket: Socket): Unit = { }
    def checkClientTrusted(certs: Array[X509Certificate], authType: String, sslEngine: SSLEngine): Unit = { }
    def checkServerTrusted(certs: Array[X509Certificate], authType: String, sslEngine: SSLEngine): Unit = { }
  }

  private[this] val sslContext = {
    val context = SSLContext.getInstance("SSL")
    context.init(null, Array(new IgnorantTrustManager()), new java.security.SecureRandom())
    context
  }
```

Thanks to this article http://log.rowanto.com/java-8-turning-off-ssl-certificate-check/.
